lyrics.text:
The year is closing up 

There’s still so much I wish that I had done 

I’m sitting on my perch in the sun and I’m counting down the days

I fell in and out of love 

But I’m blessed that we still get to keep in touch 

Sienna moved a few corners down and we talk most every day 

Cherry 

She wrapped me in her arms said “I’m all yours”   

Cherry 

I really had it all but wanted more 

More 

More 

And I’ve seen Jade a couple times out at parties but we just wave with our eyes 

It’s awkward, but I guess that’s expected when you waste a good girl’s time 

And now all of those wrongs have been turned into songs 

And best friends turned into enemies 

She always saw the best in me hey 

And I still think about her most everyday 

My love 

Cherry 

I hope you found what we were looking for

Cherry 

We really had it all but I wanted more 

More 

More
